<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 01:22 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5269 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r f BC-WELLPOINT-LADN     07-18 0361
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WELLPOINT-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WELLPOINT GETS 10-POINT BOOST FROM ANALYST
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS SIEROTY 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   THOUSAND OAKS, Calif. _ Shares of WellPoint Health Networks Inc.
gained almost 10 percent Monday after a Wall Street analyst
upgraded the company's stock in a second-quarter earnings preview.
</P>
<P>
   Lehman Brothers analyst Larry Marsh raised WellPoint to a
``buy'' from ``outperform'' and elevated his price target on the
stock to $95 from $90 a share.
</P>
<P>
   Marsh cited WellPoint's solid market positioning, his belief
that the company will exceed its $1.22 earnings estimate and the
anticipated closing of WellPoint's merger with Cerulean Companies
Inc. by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
   WellPoint will report second-quarter earnings July27.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Lehman analyst must feel that the fundamentals of our
business are good and that we are meeting our customers' needs,''
said John Cygul, a spokesman with Thousand Oaks-based WellPoint.
</P>
<P>
   WellPoint announced two years ago that it would merge with
Cerulean in a transaction valued at approximately $500 million.
Cerulean operates as Blue Cross/Blue Shield of Georgia with more
than 1.7 million members.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have noted further evidence that this well-managed company
continues to enjoy very solid positioning in its markets,'' wrote
Marsh in his report.
</P>
<P>
   ``After a 12 percent growth in commercial California membership
in the first quarter of 2000, we estimate that the company's market
share is now in excess of 17 percent in large group and 25 percent
in small group and individuals,'' he said. ``This growth has come
while increasing margins slightly.''
</P>
<P>
   WellPoint has also benefited from not having to deal with a
large exposure to the Medicare market, the report said.
</P>
<P>
   ``WellPoint's Medicare membership is currently less than 3
percent of total membership, and an estimated 7 percent of
revenues, representing one of the lowest percentages in the
industry,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of WellPoint gained $7.438, or 9.9 percent, to close
Monday at $82.875 on heavy volume of 1,246,800 shares on the New
York Stock Exchange.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-18-00 0122EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
