<HEADLINE>
COTTON SEARCHING FOR HOOP HOME
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SEAN KEARNS  
 c.2000 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONG BEACH, Calif. _ Finding a basketball home has never come
easy for Schea Cotton, and in his first three weeks as a
professional basketball player that hasn't changed.
</P>
<P>
   Cotton went from a second-round hopeful to not being drafted. He
played one game for an agent team at the Summer Pro League.
</P>
<P>
   He later was picked up by the Orlando Magic summer-league team.
But the untimely death of Conrad McRae during practice last week
ended the Magic's summer season.
</P>
<P>
   Then Cotton played his first game Monday as a member of the
Golden State Warriors' summer team.
</P>
<P>
   It seemed that every college recruited Cotton out of St. John
Bosco High, including UCLA. He played one season at Alabama before
declaring for the NBA draft. But he wasn't selected.
</P>
<P>
   As a member of the Magic summer team, Cotton was becoming
friends with McRae. Toward the end of the Magic's first practice,
Cotton saw McRae fall face first. At first, Cotton thought McRae
was playing some kind of joke. About three hours after McRae's
death, the Magic had a team meeting and disbanded the summer-league
team.
</P>
<P>
   Cotton was once again without a team until the Warriors picked
him up.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
