   TECH-ASIANS (Mountain View, Calif.) _ Between 1995 and 1998
nearly 3 in 10 companies started in Silicon Valley had Asian
founders, according to a study. Asians _ from China, Taiwan, Hong
Kong, India, Pakistan and other South and Southeast Asian countries
_ account for a little more than 10 percent of California's overall
population. By Alex Pham. 1670 words. GRAPHIC: 38 picas x 3 inches,
``An Asian upswing.''
</P>
