Newhouse News Service for Tuesday, July 18. For information about
purchasing articles as a ``separate-buy, contact Debra Weydert of
the New York Times Syndicate at 1-732-390-4480; fax, 732-390-4697;
e-mail: weyded(at)nytimes.com.)
<TEXT>
<P>
   GRIZZLY-WARS _ If wildlife advocates and federal biologists have
their way, Ol' Silvertip -- the grizzly bear -- will soon start a
slow march through the Bitterroot Mountains, jump-started by a
proposed government program to inject captured bears back into this
former home range. That prospect puts many area residents on the
battlements of yet another campaign in the ongoing Western war over
endangered species. Photos, graphic. About 2,300
</P>
<P>
   DRUGCO-DISTRUST _ To an extent, the heated rhetoric labeling
drug makers as price gougers and profiteers reflects election-year
politics. But politicians, consumer advocates and health-care
experts say growing distrust of pharmaceutical companies may keep
them on the defensive well beyond the November elections. Drug
makers say they are misunderstood. About 1,000
</P>
