</P>
<P>
   FRANCE-WINE-MANAGE (Aniane, France) _ America is famous for its
corporate marketing. Think Coke and McDonald's. France is famous
for its fine wines. Think Chateau Yquem and Chateau LaTour. Now,
imagine a U.S. marketing juggernaut like the Robert Mondavi Winery
traipsing into a French village that prides itself on its ancient
vintages. Such a Yankee intrusion just might arouse a firestorm of
opposition from locals, and that is exactly what has happened. By
Vivienne Walt.
</P>
<P>
   TOURDEFRANCE-MARKETING (Courchevel, France) _ A convoy of
marketers' vehicles precedes the Tour de France, allowing 40
advertisers ranging from Credit Lyonnais to makers of pork pate to
spend millions giving away products to spectators. By Samuel Abt.
</P>
<P>
   AETNA-EARNINGS (Undated) _ Aetna warned Tuesday that it expected
its second-quarter earnings to fall as much as 29 percent shy of
Wall Street's estimates because of higher medical costs and more
hospital visits by the people it covers. By Milt Freudenheim.
</P>
<P>
