<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IT'S JUST NOT THE `RIDE' IT COULD HAVE BEEN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Ride With the Devil'' (DVD) _ Ang Lee's Civil
War epic would seem to have everything going for it. It's set in
Missouri, where the guerrilla battles between Southern sympathizers
and the Yankees provide enough action and historical ambiguity to
satisfy the most demanding viewers. But there's a real problem.
It's style. The actors are just too clean to be convincing
19th-century hell-raisers. The long locks on the men look as if
they just had a double herbal rinsing in the hairdresser's trailer.
Even when one character gets his finger shot off, it's
spectacularly unconvincing.
</P>
<P>
   ``Angela's Ashes'' _ Frank McCourt's touchingly tough memoir
loses a lot in its translation to the screen. McCourt's prose,
which delicately bridged the abyss between sentimentality and
despair, was obviously sacrificed to the needs of the cinema. While
reading the book, readers create their own mental movie. In this
case, seeing is not necessarily believing. Somewhere along the way,
the magic disappeared.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW ON DVD: ``Harold and Maude'' (1971) _ Hal Ashby, who went on
to direct films such as ``Shampoo'' and ``Being There,'' made this
charming, offbeat movie about a nutty kid named Harold, who lives
to talk about death, and a crazy old lady named Maude. While the
dark comedy has lost some of its edge over the past three decades,
Ruth Gordon's portrayal of Maude is marvelously cranky. Bud Cort,
who went on to repeat variations of the nutty loner in subsequent
films, makes for a suitable companion. Some of the key principals _
notably Ashby and Gordon _ have died, and with this restriction on
what commentary could be provided, the DVD producers elected not to
include the usual additional features. (It would have been
interesting to hear a commentary track by Cort.) But the print is
pristine and the sound quality superb, so those who just want to
see an old favorite in mint condition should be content.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: July 25: ``Magnolia'' (DVD), ``The Beach,''
``The Perfect Tenant,'' ``Drowning Mona,'' ``Bruce Brown Surf
Collection,'' ``The Secret of Roan Inish'' (DVD), ``Space Jam''
(DVD). Aug. 1: ``The Brothers Quay Collection'' (DVD). Aug. 8:
``Reindeer Games,'' ``Holy Smoke,'' ``The Grandfather.'' Aug. 15:
``It's the Rage,'' ``Ghost Dog'' (DVD). Aug. 22: ``The Tigger
Movie'' (DVD), ``Mifune.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
