   JERUSALEM-STATUS (Jerusalem) _ On the hot, dusty streets of the
Old City, where Jew and Muslim (not to mention Christians) insist
that Jerusalem must be theirs alone, finding a compromise on the
city's status seems all but impossible. But visit places like the
maternity ward at Hadassah hospital, where Israeli and Palestinian
mothers give birth side by side and their families mingle in
comfortable harmony, and it becomes possible to envision a workable
future. By Charles M. Sennott. 1730 words.
