<P>
   MIDEAST-TALKS (Thurmont, Md.) _ The White House painted a
picture Tuesday of little sleep and unwavering intensity inside the
gates of Camp David, describing scenes of President Clinton
negotiating until dawn with Prime Minister Ehud Barak of Israel and
then, after a catnap, meeting with Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
five hours later. Informally, officials were suggesting that
Clinton's artificial deadline of 9 a.m. Wednesday, when he is
scheduled to leave for Japan, could be stretched by as much as 21
hours, an element of information that added to a steadily building
drama. By Jane Perlez.
</P>
