<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-POPMUSIC-FERMAN-COLUMN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BRITNEY MANIA: AT 18, SHE'S ON TOP OF THE WORLD 
 (ACCOMPANIED BY BC-MIKAILA-TEX)
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service Clients) 
 By DAVE FERMAN 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   It's Britney Spears' world _ we just live in it, buy the CDs,
and circulate the hot rumors.
</P>
<P>
   At 18, Spears is a small-town girl who made good _ incredibly
good. In the past two years she has sold more than 16 million CDs
and become the reigning queen of all young female singers with bare
midriffs.
</P>
<P>
   She's accomplished all this in large part because of her looks
and her persona _ just-slightly-naughty nice girl _ and a sound
that's a squeaky clean version of modern R&AMP;B, topped by her squeaky
clean voice.
</P>
<P>
   Britney is back in Fort Worth-Dallas at 7:30 CDT Wednesday
night, when she'll play the Smirnoff Music Centre in Dallas. She is
touring to support her second CD, ``Oops!... I Did It Again,''
which has sold more than 4 million copies in only six weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Here, then, is the latest about Britney:
</P>
<P>
   Britney museum &QC;
</P>
<P>
   People at the Kentwood Museum in Kentwood, La., _ Britney's
hometown _ are going to devote one room of the museum to
memorabilia of Britney's career. The museum currently features
antiques and an exhibit about local veterans, from World War II to
Desert Storm.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're planning on having platinum records and dolls and
clothes and the necklace she wore in the Mardi Gras parade,'' says
museum employee Hazel Morris. ``We don't have things from her
family here yet, but it's been promised.''
</P>
<P>
   Will there be a specific theme? ``No, it's just Britney,''
Morris said. ``You don't need a theme. We're planning on this being
open next year _ I think she'll be here at the opening. That's the
impression I have.''
</P>
<P>
   But Morris added that there is nothing to see yet. ``I have
people calling and dropping in and I'm tellin' you, I have so many
disappointed people,'' she said. ``All I can show them now are
photos of her grandfathers in the military exhibit. You'd be
surprised how many people want to see those.''
</P>
<P>
   Britney vs. Christina &QC;
</P>
<P>
   There is definitely competition between Britney and Christina
Aguilera for the honor of Most Popular Blond Teen Singer.
</P>
<P>
   Britney has sold 16 million CDs to Christina's 6 million,
although Britney has made two CDs, Christina just one.
</P>
<P>
   Both have made the cover of ``Rolling Stone:'' Britney in a
red-white-and-blue top and red pants, Christina in a tank top,
jeans, and a bikini bottom.
</P>
<P>
   Britney has been the grand marshal of New Orleans' Mardi Gras
Parade.
</P>
<P>
   Christina beat Britney for the Best New Artist Grammy this past
February.
</P>
<P>
   Britney has hosted ``Saturday Night Live'' (and was actually
pretty funny).
</P>
<P>
   Britney has become part of Cockney slang: A ``Britney Spears''
now means ``beer'' in various bars in England.
</P>
<P>
   Christina is the better singer.
</P>
<P>
   Britney factoids &QC;
</P>
<P>
   She performed in talent shows as a child; during the summer, she
would head to New York to study at the off-Broadway Dance Center
and the Professional Performing Arts School.
</P>
<P>
   When she was only 10, she appeared off-Broadway in ``Ruthless''
_ inspired by the movie ``The Bad Seed.''
</P>
<P>
   She was a part of ``The Mickey Mouse Club Show'' for two years.
</P>
<P>
   Her rise to popularity began with mall tours with 'N Sync.
</P>
<P>
   With the success of ``Baby, One More Time,'' she became the
youngest performer ever to hit the top of the charts with a single
and an album.
</P>
<P>
   She recently purchased, for seven figures, a mansion and estate
in England.
</P>
<P>
   Her record company has vigorously denied reports in the British
tabloids that Britney and 'N Sync's Justin Timberlake were either
engaged or had been secretly married.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
