<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   FAT-SOUTHERNERS _We know that America overall has a weight
problem - by some measures, 50 percent of the population is at
least somewhat overweight. But what's the Southern piece of that
pie? According to a new AJC poll, Southerners are more likely than
people elsewhere in the US to admit to being ``moderately or
seriously'' overweight - even though they set the bar for what
constitutes ``overweight'' higher than residents of other states
do, and given even more latitude to men than they do to women. At
the same time, though, Southerners are more willing to blame their
own bad habits for their weight problems. Includes interviews with
poll respondents and Southern sociologists. With charts, possible
photos. (McKenna, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   CAR-TECH _Video games, DVD players and even the PC are moving
out of the home and onto the road, which has made owning a simple
CD or cassette player for your set of wheels last century's news.
Luxuries usually strewn about the family room are becoming popular
gadgets in cars and in roomy SUVs. Ever since Oldsmobile introduced
a videocassette player for its minivans in 1998, car-stereo
enthusiasts have been adding more dazzle to audio systems with the
addition of video. And the automotive world is jumping the
bandwagon; every major manufacturer now offers video in the car.
(Dayton Daily News) WITH PHOTOS
</P>
