<P>
   CoxNet will move three stories tonight on the death of Georgia
Sen. Paul Coverdell, who passed away early this evening at the age
of 61.
</P>
<P>
   The following is a budget of the stories moving from the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution this evening:
</P>
<P>
   COVERDELL-MAIN _ Sen. Paul Coverdell, the fourth-leading
Republican in the Senate and the Senate liaison for George W.
Bush's presidential campaign, died Tuesday. He was 61. The Georgia
Republican had surgery Monday to relieve pressure on his brain from
a cerebral hemorrhage. The senator, who had reported no serious
health problems in the past, was admitted Saturday night after
complaining of severe headaches. Coverdell built a reputation as an
effective, behind-the-scenes operative for Senate Republicans,
working long hours to
</P>
<P>
   organize his colleagues into a unified voice. (Foskett, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   COVERDELL-OBIT _ A detailed look at the career and life of the
Georgia senator.
</P>
<P>
   (Judd, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COVERDELL-MEDIA _ Early media reports pronunced Sen. Coverdell
dead before the hospital said he died. How did that happen?
(Druckenmiller, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   Journal-Constitution) MOVING LATE _ AFTER 10 p.m.
</P>
