   SENATE-MARRIAGE-TAX (Washington) _ The Senate passes a tax cut
for married couples, taking a big step in the election-year push by
Republicans to highlight their differences with Democrats over what
to do with the federal budget surplus. The vote was 61-38, with
eight Democrats joining Republicans to approve the measure, which
would reduce taxes for nearly all married couples by $248 billion
over the next 10 years. By Richard W. Stevenson. (We plan to move
the story by 8:15 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.) 1,200 words.
