of little sleep and unwavering intensity inside the gates of Camp
David. Informally, officials are suggesting that Clinton's
artificial deadline of 9 a.m. Wednesday, when he is scheduled to
leave for Japan, could be stretched by as much as 21 hours, an
element of information that added to a steadily building drama. By
