squeezing nearly every household, the Consumer Price Index jumped
by 0.6 of a percent in June, the Labor Department reports. But
apart from energy, inflation remained mild. By Louis Uchitelle.
(Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``f'' news file.) 1,200 words.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-EMAIL-SURVEILLANCE (London) _ As the Clinton
administration formally enters the debate about law enforcement
surveillance in cyberspace, the British government is about to
enact a law that would give the authorities here broad powers to
intercept and decode e-mail messages and other communications
between companies, organizations and individual citizens. By Sarah
Lyall. (The story has moved in ``i'' news file.) 1,700 words.
</P>
<P>
   OBIT-COVERDELL _ Sen. Paul Coverdell, R-Ga., a congressional
workhorse who quickly ascended to a leadership post and served as
the Senate point man for longtime friend George W. Bush, died
Tuesday at 61. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
(early summary from wires)
