a cerebral hemorrhage. The senator, who had reported no serious
health problems in the past, was admitted Saturday night after
complaining of severe headaches. Coverdell built a reputation as an
effective, behind-the-scenes operative for Senate Republicans,
working long hours to
</P>
<P>
   organize his colleagues into a unified voice. (Foskett, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   COVERDELL-OBIT _ A detailed look at the career and life of the
Georgia senator.
</P>
