   (NYT1) NEW YORK -- July 18, 2000 -- ONLINE-INVESTMENT-CLUBS
-- Offline or online, the intent of investment clubs now seems about
the same as it ever was: to learn. "People are craving ways to bring
other people into their investing experience, that's why the stock
discussion sites are so popular," says Ion Yadigaroglu, 30,
co-founder and chief executive of Bivio, a new Internet company based
in Boulder, Colo. Yadigaroglu in Times Square. (Ruby Washington/The
New York Times) *Story moved on 071700*
