<SLUG> BC-FBN--HOUSTON-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
Houston NFL team sets preseason foes
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; By JOHN McCLAIN &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; c. 2000, Houston Chronicle &LR;  &QL; 
If everything goes according to plan and construction is completed
on time, Houston's NFL expansion team will play for the first time
in the new 69,000-seat, retractable-roof stadium against the Miami
Dolphins in the fourth preseason game of the 2002 season.
</P>
<P>
   Bob McNair's expansion team, which will begin play in a newly
realigned NFL in 2002, does not have an official nickname, a head
coach or a division to join, but it does have an inaugural
five-game preseason schedule.
</P>
<P>
   After making its debut in the nationally televised Pro Football
Hall of Fame Game at Canton, Ohio, against an opponent to be
determined _ Kansas City is McNair's first choice _ Houston visits
Denver and Dallas and hosts Miami and Tampa Bay.
</P>
<P>
   ``Bob and I sat down and came up with a plan for that first
preseason, and we think we've got a good schedule,'' general
manager Charley Casserly said. ``We wanted to schedule good
franchises that produce the kind of teams that'll be attractive to
our fans.
</P>
<P>
   ``No one knows for sure how good teams are going to be in 2002
because of the system (free agency and the salary cap), but we've
scheduled solid organizations that should continue to have good
teams and be top draws.''
</P>
<P>
   McNair and Dallas Cowboys owner Jerry Jones plan to play an
annual preseason game on a home-and-home basis. Houston has
four-year preseason deals with Denver and Tampa Bay. Miami is
scheduled for the first two years and will be replaced by Kansas
City in 2004 and 2005.
</P>
<P>
   McNair also has a close relationship with Broncos owner Pat
Bowlen, who is chairman of the expansion committee. Houston and
Denver will play in new stadiums in 2002.
</P>
<P>
   As the 32nd franchise, Houston will be part of a realigned NFL
that will have eight divisions of four teams each.
</P>
<P>
   The owners are a long way from determining the new divisions,
but Casserly had to take the possibilities into consideration when
setting the preseason schedule.
</P>
<P>
   ``We don't know what division we're going to be in, but we've
been told we'll be in the AFC,'' Casserly said. ``One proposal has
us playing in the AFC Central with Pittsburgh, Cleveland and
Cincinnati.
</P>
<P>
   ``Another has us in a new division with Jacksonville,
Indianapolis and Tennessee. The first thing was to take all of them
off the preseason list.''
</P>
<P>
   The dates and times haven't been determined for games in that
first preseason, but the order is set. Because the stadium is
supposed to be ready in August 2002, Denver and Dallas had to be
scheduled on the road.
</P>
<P>
   When McNair's team, which is expected to be named the Texans,
travels to Canton for its debut in late July, the Pro Football Hall
of Fame Game should be in its fourth year of being played on Monday
Night Football.
</P>
<P>
   In its second game, Houston visits the Broncos, who will be
playing their second season in the new 75,000-seat stadium that is
under construction next to Mile High Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   On the third weekend of preseason, Houston and Dallas will play
for the first time. McNair and Jones have forged the kind of
enterprising relationship that should be exciting for NFL fans in
Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Both teams will have training camp in Texas. McNair and Jones
would like to see them practice against each other and perhaps
scrimmage early in camp before they play the game.
</P>
<P>
   After the Cowboys game, Houston's new stadium, which is being
built next to the Astrodome, should be ready for Miami.
</P>
<P>
   McNair has said he plans to have a special section underneath
his suite reserved for former Oilers players and coaches. Perhaps
Bum Phillips and Don Shula could be brought back as honorary
captains.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know Houston and Miami had a good rivalry for a long time,''
Casserly said. ``We thought bringing in the Dolphins for that first
game would be exciting for the fans.''
</P>
<P>
   The last preseason game is against Tampa Bay.
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
</TEXT>
